The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, February 02, 2004  Calcutta Column
 
	A large sum has been earmarked for the upkeep of Vidyasagar  Setu, but most of the gully pits remain choked round the  year. The piers supporting the bridge have creepers climbing  up, which is extremely dangerous, as some of the shrubs  can damage the foundation of the structure. 
	 Mousumee Das Majumdar, Nakuleswar Bhattacharya  Lane.  
	The South Dum Dum Municipality has taken no steps to desilt  the Bagjola canal, despite several reminders. The stagnant  water here breeds mosquitoes. A proper outflow channel is  needed before the monsoon.  
	Jyoti Bakshi, Heysham Row. 

